beer_description:
With a deep amber colour, this bold and refreshing ale blends seven specialty malts. Three hop additions of Nugget, Cascade, Willamette and Centennial hops, now dry-hopped, to give this ale a distinctive hop aroma and bitterness, classic to style.

Year round brew. 6*355ml cans, 12*355ml Sampler & 50L Kegs in BC & Alberta.
This well-balanced Pale Ale is a combination of both European and Northwest American hops. Golden color and floral bite a result of beautifully balanced hops.

The holidays at Tr?egs start with our inner Mad Elf momentarily taking over the brew deck. So blame "him" for this cheerful ruby red creation brewed with honey, cherries and Belgian yeast reminiscent of cinnamon, clove and allspice.

The holidays at Tr?egs start with our inner Mad Elf momentarily taking over the brew deck. So blame "him" for this cheerful ruby red creation brewed with honey, cherries and Belgian yeast reminiscent of cinnamon, clove and allspice.

An English style cream ale fashioned after the classic "Milk of Manchester" - Boddingtons.  This light colored ale is crafted with Maris Otter pale malt and a generous addition of honey malt.  Traditional English Fuggle and East Kent Golding hops balance this beer, giving it a smooth and easy to drink character.
Big with a pleasing malt sweetnes and hints of peat and smoke.
Winter seasonal.

Tasting Notes:
Above and beyond an India Pale Ale?I2PA is radically hopped with an intense aroma and hop bitterness.

8 Ingredients:
100% Floor Malted Maris Otter Pale Malt, Great Western 2-Row Malt; Saaz, Northwest Golding, Perle, & Cascade Hops; Free Range Coastal Water & Pacman Yeast

Food Pairing: Pork, Beef

HISTORY
The creation of India Pale Ale (IPA) during the early 1700s was the result of tremendous efforts by British brewers to overcome a difficult problem: during the 1700s beer did not keep well on long ocean voyages, especially into hot climates. These hot environments resulted in the arrival of flat, sour beer.

beer_description: For the 666th batch of their English 6 Grain Ale, they tripled the malt & hops for this thick, sweet 9.3% beauty.

A light Amber Ale flavored with real cocoa nibs.
Meant to pair with our food menu and brewed as 
our house beer.

OMB?s flagship, Copper, is an authentic D?sseldorf style ?Altbier? or Amber Ale. There are no crazy flavors or gimmicks with Copper ? its full-flavored start transitions to a smooth, balanced, easy-drinking finish. It?s the beer that tastes like beer.

Question: What do you get if you blend Hardcore IPA and I Beat You together and then add even more dry hops?

Answer: I Hardcore You. Introducing a new type of collaboration from Mikkeller and BrewDog.
 
I Hardcore You is a 9.5% Imperial India Pale Ale, an international collaborative effort between 2 of Europe's most rock 'n roll brewers. This beer is a blend of BrewDog?s Hardcore IPA and Mikkeller?s I Beat You (2 of our favourite beers). After the blending, the beer isthen dry hopped a further 2 times. Making I Hardcore You a beer which has been dry hopped four times, or maybe even six times.

We kinda lost count.
A dark Munich lager beer
With the balance of malt and hops patterned after classic English pale ales, S.P.A. is Wellington?s best seller as a draught.

Watch out!  This huge new IPA is coming at you ready to literally cram hops down your throat! This monster weighs in at a hefty 6.5% alc/vol, 65 IBUs and uses 4 different hop varieties, in whole leaf and pellet in 6 different additions. We use a healthy dose of Caramunich malt to give this beer a bright orange color and enough body to balance the hops. We use cutting edge hop varieties to create a crazy mix of pineapple, grapefruit and pine aromas that just screams American IPA. This awesome ale pairs well with other strong flavors such as aged natural cheeses, spicy sushi, curry, etc. Truly an IPA that sets a new standard for brewers and beer lovers on both coasts Cheers.

Our winter stout is brewed with ten different malts to create a complex and distinctive beer. We add organic fair-trade coffee, which is specially produced for Big Boss by coffee experts Larry's Beans. We offer this synergistic seasonal brew for a limited time in the winter season. Get a pint of this full flavor stout while it is available.

This foreboding black ale unleashes a torrential downpour of hop character within a maelstrom of roasted malt flavor. A pleasing roundness and satisfying balance offer but the illusion of safe shelter. This monster stout is not for the faint of heart.

beer_description: Smooth, robust, with a natural deep red color.

Paradise Road is the namesake of our clean and crisp Bohemian style lager. Our golden pilsner is inspired by Paradise Road's natural elements of refreshing streams and waterfalls and a place where you want to relax and drink a beer.

A slight citrus hop flavor is balanced by a light body and crisp malt profile. A combination of citrusy Yakima grown hops and six varieties of barley provide a depth of complexity that begs another sip.

Our winter ale is made from a blend of pale, caramel and chocolate malts with each contributing an interesting malt character reminiscent of a traditional English Old Ale. We then add a NW twist by aggressively hopping this ale to provide contrast to the malty body.

Characterized by chocolate malt flavors, this full bodied ale is appropriately dark in color. A subtle hop bitterness is accompanied by a healthy addition of caramel and chocolate malts. Cascade hops provide a flowery and aromatic hop finish.
An array of brown, roasted and caramel malts create this rich and malty ale. A small addition of peat smoked barley adds a subtle layer of intrigue to this local favorite.
Un-filtered variant of Kunstmann's Lager

Our English style Barley Wine has a pronounced malt body to go along with a sincere NW bitterness and fruity finish that will warm you up on a cold, rainy day! The higher alcohol content allows this ale to age nicely for up to five years.
Dark Chocolate and Roasted malts introduce you to flavors of coffee and coco. Our Stout is lightly hopped and conditioned with Nitrogen to allow for a creamy and smooth draft experience.
Fuggle and Golding hops lend authenticity to this traditional English style Pale ale. A kiss of dark crystal malt helps to distinguish this ale from just any Pale!
This crisp and refreshing tawny colored ale has an impeccable hop bitterness followed by a slightly lingering citrus hop finish.
A crisp English style IPA, this approachable India Pale is a perfect harmony of pale maltiness and assertive hop flavor. Our most popular beer in Port Townsend.

The Beast is a seducer - accomodating, complicated, powerful, dark and created to last the ages. Beyond this, it?s futile to attempt to describe Him. He will unveil Himself differently to each of His followers. The mark is in His constitution. Brewed with two-row malted barley, honey malt, and imported Belgian specialty grains (aromatic, pale wheat, roasted wheat, and Special B), hops (Magnum, Galena, Saaz, Hallertau, Tettnang, and Hersbrucker), brewing sugars (raisins, dates, blackstrap molasses, alfalfa honey, turbinado, and dark Belgian candy sugar), water, Belgian yeast and another hellion of a yeast strain.OG: 1.138

beer_description: Brewed exclusively for the Bahama Breeze Caribbean style restaurant chain by the Specialty Brewing Group of Anheuser-Busch.

In tribute to Chief Chetzemoka we named our Golden Ale. This easy drinking light ale is comprised mostly of NW Pilsner malt with a little wheat and Vienna malt to go along with the Hallertau variety hops. Ale to the Chief!

The Runaway Red Ale is a rich full bodied amber ale with a delicate fruity flavor. The sweetness with carefully balanced with Willamette and Tettnanger hops from the Yakima Valley. This beer derives its color and caramel flavor from Crystal and Carastan malts. A delicious beer for the real beer drinker.
Copious amounts of dark and sweet malt give our Stout aromas of coffee and a rich mouthfeel with a dry finish.

Stone Smoked Porter w/ Chipotle Peppers is a thing of spicy glory, with the just-right heat of smoked jalape?os (aka chipotles) that combines beautifully with the beer's peat-smoked malt and roasty character. The idea came about in 2006 when Merchandise Manager Chris Carroll suggested we make a special "South of the Border Stone Smoked Porter" for Cinco de Mayo that year. One sip, and we were hooked!
beer_name: Stone Smoked Porter w/ Chipotle Peppers

beer_description: This big Citra hop brew will fill your nose with sweet citrus aroma & a nice crystal malt black notes. Its deep gold color has a slight haze from massive amounts of hops used to brew our hoppiest brew.

This brew pours a darker amber color with a very generous amount of head.  Great retention and great lacing. Right from the start you know this beer is good as soon as you take a whiff.  It?s a clean smell full of citrus and grassy hops. It also has a nice caramel malt background with some honey added in. Smells really good. The taste and mouthfeel are even better. Grassy and citrus bittering hops. It has a bitter and dry feel at the same time.  All three things, the hops, the dryness, and bitterness are all just right. Not extreme but not wimpy either. The caramel malt background and honey just add to the fantastic taste. This beer is just crisp and clean.

COMMERCIAL DESCRIPTION
Limited (brewed once). Brewed exclusively for Stockholm Beer bar Akkurat?s 15th anniversary. Brewed in March 2010. 112? Plato. Matured on oak casks for 10 months, 5 of them on Cognac casks. Bottled on December 1st 2010. Pre-released fromkeg at Borefts Beer Festival 2010.

A beer that truly started Samuel Adam's odyssey into extreme brewing. Its deep, full flavor explodes with notes of maple, vanilla, oak and toffee. This flavor, along with the rich mouth feel, has drawn comparisons to a vintage port, sherry, and cognac; and Samuel Adams Triple Bock should be enjoyed in much the same way. We recommend serving it at room temperature in a snifter a few ounces at a time - one bottle should generously serve two to three.  Its warming malt character and fruit esters make it an ideal after dinner aperitif.

There have been only three vintages produced: 1994, 1995 and 1997. 1994 and 1995 vintages are marked as such on the back label; 1997 vintage is not.
Hybrid beer between a Barleywine and an American Wheat ale, Part of the Big Beer Series.

beer_description: Evolved from 20th Anniversary Imperial IPA. Polished brass with copper tints and a wavy, dense tan head. Aromas of pink grapefruit, fresh huckleberry pie, redwood needles, caramel, and woodruff greet the nose. The expected bitterness is delivered on the palate, as are rich flavors of candied grapefruit peel, fresh pine, blueberries, black pepper, vanilla, and digestive biscuits balanced beautifully with malty richness and body. Long, warm, herbal finish.

Rich and malty, Double Dee complements our High Esteem with a modest bump of malt presence, alcohol, and residual sweetness. Brewed with an addition of kettle sugar, the flavor is toasty and nutty with a hint of raisins, and is balanced by an herbal hop finish.
Brewed with two different chocolate malts giving it a smooth, still complex taste.

The intensely smooth and rich roasted flavor is complemented by the unmistakable pretence of hops.

The bitterness is held in check, preserving the flavors of dark chocolate. 

This ale is aggressively dry hopped with Citra to cut through it all. Hail Santa.
Medium-bodied with a firm bitterness and pronounced hop flavor and aroma. Brewed from American Centennial hops. making it more sweet than bitter.

Toasty-Nutty-Hoppy: The term "nut brown" stems from the color of brown ales rather than the use of actual nuts in the recipe. Traditional English brown ales exhibit mild hop notes and toasty, nutty flavors given by the malt. Our Americanized brown ale leans more on the piney, dank American hop character, balanced by a nearly chocolaty, dry malt backbone.
Blend of Working Man's Lunch and Hogwash available at the Brewery.

Ale La Reverend is a distinctively dry and light bodied Indian Pale Ale with an appealing golden hue. It has a thirst-quenching crispness and is laden with citrus and spruce hop aromas. Semi-sweet malt provides a backdrop for mild earthy flavors and slight grassy notes. Double dry-hop additions allows for a lower alcohol level while still providing the entire hop effect expected of a classic IPA.

A light, clean, easy drinking Hefeweizen. This beer is categorized by a grain bill of 50% malted wheat and a German wizen yeast strain that is directly responsible for the distinctly complex flavors. Immediately evident in the nose, this brew is punctuated by esters of banana and clove. These aromatics reflect similar flavors detected during consumption.
Easy-drinking, smooth, and flavorful. Your everyday beer!

Swiss Amber Ale is a classic example of an amber ale.  Caramel malts create the rich red color and complex flavors that prevail in this refreshingly drinkable amber ale. It is made in small batches with specialty 2 row malts and a combination of hops to create a perfect balance of flavors.
Light amber in color, this beer has a unique blend of hop flavor with medium full body and exhibits smoke taste reflective from the use of specialty beechwood smoked malt.

Brewed in the strictest rules of art, Belle Gueule Original is a light bodied lager with a refined aroma. In a frank golden color, Belle Gueule marries a remarkable bitterness and sweetness.
